ly for LINEAR/XYK curves, then if `_cost(...)` is greater than `msg.value` it clamps `cost` down to `msg.value` instead of reducing `amount`. The buyer still receives the full overshot token amount.","impact":"Exact-in buyers can obtain more sale inventory than they actually paid for. Even if each trade only extracts rounding-sized value, the discrepancy is repeatable and drains DAO sale inventory at a discount.","paths":["Configure a LINEAR or XYK bonding-curve sale.","Call `buyExactIn()` with a value that makes the analytical `amount` slightly too large once `_cost(...)` is recomputed with rounded-up pricing.","The function sets `cost = msg.value`, spends allowance for the oversized `amount`, and transfers all of those shares/loot to the buyer."]},{"id":"F-003","severity":"Low","confidence":"medium","title":"Proposal-threshold checks use current votes while snapshots use the previous block, enabling same-block threshold bypass","locations":["Moloch.sol:283","Moloch.sol:285","Moloch.sol:290","Moloch.sol:347"],"claim":"`openProposal()` enforces `proposalThreshold` with `getVotes(msg.sender)` from the current block, but fixes the proposal snapshot at `block.number - 1`. A proposer can temporarily acquire delegated votes in the current block, open the proposal, and then be evaluated against a snapshot where those votes never existed.","impact":"The proposal threshold no longer reliably gates proposal creation. Attackers can use transient voting power to open spam proposals they could not have opened at the actual voting snapshot, which also compounds with any features triggered on proposal open.","paths":["Temporarily obtain enough delegated votes in the current block.","Call `openProposal()` or `castVote()` (which auto-opens) before the borrowed votes disappear.","The threshold passes on current votes, while the proposal snapshot is fixed to the previous block where the proposer did not hold those votes."]}]
